659
00:51:17,697 --> 00:51:19,998
Do you recognize him?

660
00:51:19,998 --> 00:51:23,007
I've only seen him around here.

661
00:51:23,007 --> 00:51:25,377
You shouldn't ask me.

662
00:51:26,208 --> 00:51:28,348
Oh, there he is.

663
00:51:28,348 --> 00:51:30,517
He was close to that customer.

664
00:51:31,748 --> 00:51:34,047
Yes, thank you.

665
00:51:42,157 --> 00:51:44,427
Yoon Ki is

666
00:51:44,427 --> 00:51:48,697
already pretending like he's an abdicated king who put his son on the throne.

667
00:51:49,537 --> 00:51:51,338
You should've seen him, Oppa Young Ki.

668
00:51:51,338 --> 00:51:54,708
Then you'll probably put a halt on the board meeting

669
00:51:54,708 --> 00:51:57,938
and the financial holding company.

670
00:51:57,938 --> 00:52:00,608
He can't even hold to what he has.

671
00:52:00,608 --> 00:52:03,007
He doesn't have enough power.

672
00:52:10,618 --> 00:52:12,357
Well...

673
00:52:13,387 --> 00:52:16,997
Do you still feel sour about it?

674
00:52:16,997 --> 00:52:19,568
I'm very disappointed, too.

675
00:52:19,568 --> 00:52:22,598
I didn't bring that up just to benefit myself.

676
00:52:22,598 --> 00:52:24,337
What?

677
00:52:25,237 --> 00:52:26,968
I mean...

678
00:52:26,968 --> 00:52:28,807
No one else in the world may know,

679
00:52:28,807 --> 00:52:34,147
but the three of us, we three siblings know how cruel our father is.

680
00:52:34,907 --> 00:52:39,718
All our lives, he’s lined us up in front of him, evaluating us every single day.

681
00:52:39,718 --> 00:52:45,417
And he now wants to abandon us and go with Do Jun?

682
00:52:45,417 --> 00:52:50,927
Why should we put in hard work to give a feast to a stray dog like him?

683
00:52:53,128 --> 00:52:54,827
You must call off the board meeting first.

684
00:52:54,827 --> 00:52:58,668
It's a great chance. We can use Father's illness as an excuse.

685
00:52:58,668 --> 00:53:03,168
He'll stop talking about the financial holding company in just three months.

686
00:53:03,168 --> 00:53:06,578
What if Father wakes up?

687
00:53:08,108 --> 00:53:12,518
Do you think he'll forgive the three of us for the coup?

688
00:53:16,487 --> 00:53:19,757
We'll hold the board meeting as planned.

689
00:53:20,695 --> 00:53:25,788
And we'll put mercenaries in the front of our coup.

690
00:53:25,788 --> 00:53:27,527
Mercenaries?

691
00:53:32,097 --> 00:53:35,537
They're holding the board meeting as planned.

692
00:53:35,537 --> 00:53:37,137
- Really? 
 - Yes.

693
00:53:37,137 --> 00:53:41,308
They'll hold the meeting, but they will tamper with the votes of the directors

694
00:53:41,308 --> 00:53:43,854
to abort the attempt of building the financial holding company.

695
00:53:43,854 --> 00:53:48,847
They must feel a burden to be seen opposing your will.

696
00:53:48,847 --> 00:53:51,717
They aren't completely dull.

697
00:53:51,717 --> 00:53:55,558
It won't be easy to humor the directors for the next few days.

698
00:53:55,558 --> 00:53:57,196
But bad news.

699
00:53:57,196 --> 00:53:58,728
Once I show up

700
00:53:58,728 --> 00:54:02,398
at the board meeting, their votes are all mine.

701
00:54:03,598 --> 00:54:05,537
Once the holding company's plan passes the board meeting,

702
00:54:05,537 --> 00:54:10,537
we'll then vote to place Do Jun as a CEO candidate.

703
00:54:10,537 --> 00:54:15,307
This time, I will cast my vote on you, Mr. Lee.

704
00:54:17,878 --> 00:54:19,347
Don't worry.

705
00:54:19,347 --> 00:54:23,387
We always place an impossible candidate for the sake of the board meeting.

706
00:54:23,387 --> 00:54:26,427
That way, it won't be confusing for the shareholders

707
00:54:26,427 --> 00:54:29,558
as the management cast an overwhelming amount of votes, for a candidate they want.

708
00:54:29,558 --> 00:54:31,398
Is that right?

709
00:54:33,926 --> 00:54:38,071
So that's all settled. Be prepared for the board meeting.

710
00:54:38,071 --> 00:54:38,839
Yes.

711
00:54:38,839 --> 00:54:42,507
We should buy him a new suit to make him look sharp.

712
00:54:42,507 --> 00:54:43,838
Yes, Sir.

713
00:54:43,838 --> 00:54:46,448
I'm fine, Grandfather. Maybe next time.

714
00:54:46,448 --> 00:54:50,277
Next time? When?

715
00:54:51,078 --> 00:54:53,987
You can try to live until you're 100.

716
00:54:53,987 --> 00:54:56,107
But that "next time" never comes.

717
00:54:57,987 --> 00:55:00,858
Why isn't Mr. Woo coming back with any news?

718
00:55:00,858 --> 00:55:03,727
I'll contact him.

719
00:55:07,504 --> 00:55:10,038
Please have this as we talk.

720
00:55:10,038 --> 00:55:11,767
Sure.

721
00:55:13,444 --> 00:55:15,779
It looked like he was in debt.

722
00:55:15,779 --> 00:55:18,307
Did he tell anyone that he needed money?

723
00:55:18,307 --> 00:55:20,308
I need money, too.

724
00:55:20,308 --> 00:55:22,768
Is there anyone who doesn't need money?

725
00:55:22,768 --> 00:55:26,787
It's a rule for gamblers never to deal with money.

726
00:55:26,787 --> 00:55:28,318
Let me ask you, too.

727
00:55:28,318 --> 00:55:31,057
The police put an end to this investigation already.

728
00:55:31,057 --> 00:55:32,528
Why is Soonyang snooping around?

729
00:55:32,528 --> 00:55:35,257
This accident concerns an employee of Soonyang.

730
00:55:35,257 --> 00:55:38,597
I need to put together a report for the higher-ups.

731
00:55:38,597 --> 00:55:40,467
It must be tough for you.

732
00:55:40,467 --> 00:55:44,538
And it must've been even harder without any CCTV on the site.

733
00:55:45,398 --> 00:55:49,838
If you don't have more questions, may I go now?

734
00:55:49,838 --> 00:55:53,138
- Thank you for cooperating. 
 - Sure.

